00:04:52,090 --> 00:04:55,060
In a certain village in Congo

113
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:58,860
There was a young man called Pier Thunkai

114
00:04:56,120 --> 00:05:02,500
note: I don't know its actual transcription. It's "pieerutuukai" in katakana.

115
00:04:59,670 --> 00:07:37,860
Pier Thunkai

116
00:05:00,230 --> 00:05:03,670
One day, this young man

117
00:05:03,670 --> 00:05:05,670
Wasn't home all day

118
00:05:07,590 --> 00:05:10,510
And while he was away

119
00:05:10,510 --> 00:05:13,910
All of his property were stolen

120
00:05:15,610 --> 00:05:19,710
And so he started asking the villagers

121
00:05:19,710 --> 00:05:25,030
"Who stole all the things I had?"

122
00:05:25,630 --> 00:05:27,730
While going around from house to house

123
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:32,490
None of the villagers listened to him, though

124
00:05:34,300 --> 00:05:36,130
But unluckily for him

125
00:05:36,130 --> 00:05:38,930
At that moment, Pier Thunkai

126
00:05:39,070 --> 00:05:40,850
Accidentally slipped

127
00:05:40,850 --> 00:05:43,710
And fell down from a cliff

128
00:05:40,850 --> 00:05:45,380
note: he mistakenly says "date" instead of "gake" (cliff)

129
00:05:45,810 --> 00:05:49,810
And so, Pier Thunkai went missing

130
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:54,220
Later on, when it was night

131
00:05:54,220 --> 00:05:58,750
A monster showed up in the village

132
00:05:58,750 --> 00:06:02,590
That monster had a single eye,

133
00:06:02,590 --> 00:06:04,440
A single leg,

134
00:06:04,440 --> 00:06:05,830
And a single hand

135
00:06:05,830 --> 00:06:08,530
Every single part of his body

136
00:06:09,260 --> 00:06:10,870
Was only one of a pair

137
00:06:12,470 --> 00:06:15,400
And so, that monster

138
00:06:15,400 --> 00:06:18,010
Started asking the villagers

139
00:06:18,010 --> 00:06:21,810
"Where are all the things I had?"

140
00:06:22,340 --> 00:06:25,710
He started going from house to house

141
00:06:25,710 --> 00:06:28,720
Killing every villager he met

142
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:35,120
The villagers shouted "please, don't kill anybody else!"

143
00:06:35,820 --> 00:06:42,530
And they started to chant
a prayer to calm Pier Thunkai's anger

144
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:44,630
That song was like this:

145
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:56,940
And it repeats

146
00:07:09,390 --> 00:07:12,860
But that song didn't reach him at all

147
00:07:13,460 --> 00:07:18,300
Pier Thunkai just kept on killing each villager

148
00:07:18,300 --> 00:07:22,440
Until there was none of them left

149
00:07:23,810 --> 00:07:26,040
In Congo, to this day...

150
00:07:26,640 --> 00:07:33,180
We say "if you steal, Pier Thunkai will come for you!"

151
00:07:34,150 --> 00:07:36,680
And it came to be a common phrase

152
00:07:41,100 --> 00:07:42,890
What kind of story is that?

153
00:07:42,890 --> 00:07:45,790
It's Pier Thunkai's story

154
00:07:45,790 --> 00:07:49,260
How are Pier Thunkai and the halved monster related?

155
00:07:49,260 --> 00:07:50,070
It's the same

156
00:07:50,070 --> 00:07:51,970
Pier Thunkai himself became the monster

157
00:07:51,970 --> 00:07:54,270
He did?      - He transformed into the monster

158
00:07:54,740 --> 00:07:56,270
It came out so suddenly

159
00:07:56,270 --> 00:07:57,410
Yeah it was sudden

160
00:07:57,410 --> 00:08:01,240
But almost everyone of us got that,
like Cocorico and Yamazaki-san

161
00:08:01,240 --> 00:08:02,980
Yeah we did       - I got that

162
00:08:02,980 --> 00:08:04,440
Me too halfway

163
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:07,320
I thought I'd better off stop following it

164
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:10,490
I mean, I can't even remember
the main character's name

165
00:08:10,920 --> 00:08:13,210
Pier Thunkai, right?        - Yes

166
00:08:13,210 --> 00:08:15,390
So, he fell down a cliff
- Yeah, he fell down

167
00:08:15,390 --> 00:08:16,660
And revived as a monster

168
00:08:16,660 --> 00:08:19,070
He didn't fell down a cliff (gake)      - Huh?!

169
00:08:19,070 --> 00:08:20,900
He fell down a gliff (date)

170
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:22,600
Of course he meant "cliff"

171
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:23,730
Come on, get it

